deck: One of the world's foremost genetic engineers.
description:
Origin

As one of the world's foremost genetic engineers, Angus Hinterwald was tasked to isolate and alter a specific gene in cattle to slow the decomposition of its meat after it was processed and prepared. Instead, Hinterwald managed to isolate and identify a very rare, almost completely dormant gene that causes spontaneous combustion. And during his genetic manipulations, he created a strain of cattle whose meat would, at the first sign of decomposition, explode.

Trying to sell his invention to unscrupulous organizations, he was kidnapped by E.G.G. He was freed from his imprisonment by Tony Chu, Agent Vorhees, John Colby, Caesar Valenzano and Poyo.
name: Angus Hinterwald

deck: Judy is a victuspeciosian.

Judy Heinz-Campbell is the owner of Judy's Beauties Beauty Salon & Boutique. She's also a victuspeciosian, able to make unique preparation ouf of food to make facial beauty masks that yield amazing transformational results.

She was killed and stuffed into a freezer by a client who made herself look like Judy in order to fool Toni Chu, Caesar Valenzano and John Colby. But due to Toni's talents, she immediately arrested the client.
name: Judy Heinz-Campbell

deck: The Amazon is a playable character in Dragon's Crown and one of the subjects in the Dragon's Crown Artworks. She is a Super Strong, close ranged melee master.
description:
"Dauntless warriors who know no fear as they effortlessly wield their two-handed weapons. Their massive equipment delivers vicious blows that deal lethal damage to multiple foes at once. Lightly armored, they are agile fighters who rely on punishing kicks when unarmed." - description from Atlus' corporation.

Overview

The Amazon is a playable character in the 2013 game Dragon's Crown. She is character who's focus is on strong and relentless attacks, though she is not so good at taken damage. This makes the character a glass cannon.

Skills & Techniques

Deadly Revolution - The Amazon's aerial attack where she spins rapidly with her axe for fast multi-hitting attacks. Increase in level will increase power as well as add the ability to change direction up to four times.

Brandish - A powerful axe-spin attack that hits hard and causes knockback, making it a great combo finisher. The Amazon is also invincible while doing this. Increase in levels will increase power and add up to doing five Brandish attacks in a row.

Punisher - Ths allows the Amazon to dish out her normal ground combo faster and stronger, as well as increase the chance of gaining berserk status.

Berserk - This allows the Amazon to get berserk status while attacking and increase her power and speed while in berserk mode.
name: Amazon

deck: Crowley the cat is the familiar of Arcanna from the universe of Earth-712.
description:
Creation

Crowley the cat was created by Mark Gruenwald and first appeared as the pet of member Arcanna Jones of the Squadron Supreme #1-The Utopia Principle.

Origin

The character Arcanna, as do the other Squadron Supreme team members, are parallels to the DC Universe characters from the Justice League. As a sorceress she had her very own familiar, which is an animal with magical treats, in her case a grey cat named Crowley. Typically Crowley would stay in the company of Arcanna's family, Phillip, Drusilla, Andrew and Katrina, to safeguard them and go as a go-between between her and her family when away at missions. She shared a special mystical bond with the Jones family and was able to communicate with them all, although in what manner was never shown.
name: Crowley

deck: A Gotham city reporter, she became the Joker's first publicly known victim when he killed her during a live news broadcast.
description:
Gotham City news reporter Michelle Sanders was reporting on the reopening of Arkham Asylum when she suddenly began coughing uncontrollably. Her cough soon turned to laughter; her skin went pale and her face contorted into a rictus grin as she died on-camera. As she collapsed, the Joker appeared behind her and hijacked the broadcast, revealing himself to the citizens of Gotham for the first time. She thus holds the distinction of being the Joker's first publicly-known victim.

Although the reporter went unnamed in the actual story, her name was revealed in the book "The Batman Files."
name: Michelle Sanders

deck: A member of Fisk Industries and right-hand man to the Kingpin.
description:
Origin

Nothing is known about Wesley's origin. He was probably born and raised in or around New York City. At some point he began working for the Kingpin, and quickly rose to the position of his right-hand man.

Creation

Wesley was created by Frank Miller and David Mazzucchelli. He made his first appearance in Daredevil #227

Major Story Arcs

Born Again

Trusted to manage Kingpin's affairs, he is extremely loyal and skilled in his work managing Kingpin's criminal enterprises and affairs. Kingpin orders him to locate Nuke, and although he initially objects because of the "domestic" nature of the job, he follows through on his orders despite the difficulty he has in pulling all the required strings. When Kingpin stages Nuke's assault on Hell's Kitchen, leading to the loss of perhaps hundreds of lives, Wesley protests. This is less because of any moral qualms than a fear as to what the results of such an action may be if they are connected to it by the authorities. After the plan fails, he alerts Kingpin that Nuke has escaped his captivity. His ultimate fate is unknown.

Powers and Abilities

Wesley is a normal human and has no known superhuman powers or abilities. He appears to be quite intelligent, and to be highly diligent and competent in his work.

Other Media

Film

Daredevil

Wesley appears as Kingpin's right-hand man. His full name is given as Wesley Owen Welch. Portrayed as squeamish and cowardly, he appears to act largely as Kingpin's personal assistant. He reports the failure of Bullseye to Kingpin, and attempts to encourage his employer to increase security to deal with Daredevil's imminent arrival. When Kingpin resists he leaves the building and goes to a bar where he is confronted by Detective Nick Manolis. When offered a plea bargain he immediately betrays his employer. He is played by Leland Orser.

Television

Daredevil

Wesley appears as Fisk's right-hand man, his confidante, and his only friend, making his first appearance in "Into the Ring." His full name is given as James Wesley. For much of the series he appears as the face of his employer's organisation, and handles his interactions with his various allies and subsidiaries. He acts as Fisk's personal assistant, translator, and the manager of the day-to-day operation of his criminal enterprises. He is portrayed by Toby Leonard Moore.
